list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Minor refactor and encapsulation, added a CursorManager class with methods that change the cursor.

task.summary: Default task
Dungeon console - Initiative is now rolled only at meeting the monsters
Dungeon console - First take on buffered images
Dungeon GUI - animations on HeroClick, Monster death event now updates the icon (but then it gets overwritten by map graphics event), animation on monster hit.
Dungeon GUI - animations on monster miss is now different from monster hit, skull image is now repaired and remains on the monster after map graphics update.
Dungeon GUI - Initiative Tracker now resets on last monster kill in the room.
Dungeon - attacks now have range and clicking an attack shows the available range. Unlocking attacks to be done next.
Dungeon - ranged attacks are now working correctly
Dungeon - rooms are now revealed in a more consistent manner. Recursive distance check has better call and can now be called only once.
Added skill icons and moved skill icon todo element to character creation
Character Creator GUI - added skill icon selector to Character Creator. Minor refactoring of methods in the class
Character Creator GUI - Skill icons are now being added and read into/from HDD.
Character Creator GUI - New skill icons, small improvements to field validation, better viewing of hero icons and skill icons upon selection.
MonsterAI - new class, added some ToDos
MonsterAI - validation of fields in character creator repaired
HeroClassInformation - added a hero class information factory with class name as a constructor's parameter, added weapon and armor proficiencies to hero class information.
Performance update - hero classes enum was separated from heroinformation class and refactored into a separate class.
Performance update - enums were extracted form HeroClassInformation and put into separate classes for single responsibility and for performance.
Performance - instances of HeroClassInformation objects are replaced with respective factories. Now only lists are being passed instead of maps of lists.
Dungeon GUI - applied new cursor images. Will have to change the images some time in the future
Item Shop GUI - started working on the recognition of the weapon / armor proficiency
Item Shop GUI - Recognition of weapon / armor proficiency of buying heroes is ready
Dungeon GUI - minor corrections
Dungeon GUI - Initiative is now working, although buggy. Some setters are wrong, will have to inspect.
Dungeon GUI, Initiative Tracker - Fixed a bug with discovering a room, fixed a bug with initiative tracker, fixed the initiative tracker viewing.
Dungeon GUI - walking animation now works
Character Creator GUI - minor refactor + skill icon is being shown upon selection
DungeonGUI - refactoring of classes
DungeonGUI - Finished EncounterManager Class derived from DungeonGUI according to single responsibility principle
DungeonGUI - Damage popup is visible on hit.
DungeonGUI - Refactor into new classes
DungeonGUI - Empty fields clearing, minor refactoring
DungeonButtonEvents - beginning of Monster Round in the Initiative Order
Dungeon GUI - repaired the animations on hit and on miss
Encounter Manager - some methods were refactored from ButtonEvents class
Encounter Manager - inserting monster round into the initiative tracker, part 1
Encounter Manager - initiative order works and takes monsters into consideration
Monster AI - mock methods were created and aggression stat was introduced.
Monster AI - aggression roll is being made and distance now influences the aggression results
added new todos and changed some minor things.
Encounter and Daily Power now lock after being used. Unlocking at the next encounter is still TBD
Encounter initiative queue solved, bug fixed.
Encounter Manager - encounter powers now reset after end of encounters, daily powers reset at every three encounters
Hero powers added - daily powers updated up to Paladin
Minor corrections and todos ordering
Encounter Manager - attacking now uses the "AttackResults" class.
Encounter Manager - AoE attacks now function correctly. HP will have to be set for heroes
Encounter Manager - Single target attacks have been debugged
HeroPower Field Encapsulation, methods determining numbers of creatures hit were refactored into HeroPower class
Minor refactor and encapsulation, added a CursorManager class with methods that change the cursor.
